parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: requiring multiple turns of the key
interior lights staying on while driving
and the vehicle shutting down without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine sludge buildup can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: and sludge buildup in the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oxygen sensor failure can cause the check engine light to come on, leading to poor engine performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: oxygen sensor needing to be replaced multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power steering failure can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents.
Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents.
Water pump failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents.
Electrical system failure can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent ABS Engagement and Brake Pedal Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engagement of the ABS system and issues with the brake pedal can cause unpredictable and unreliable braking performance, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal vibrates or travels to the floor
the ABS system engages at low speeds or for no apparent reason
the vehicle shakes or vibrates when applying the brakes
the brake pedal has a spongy or soft feel
the ABS light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Rotor Failure and Excessive Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure or excessive wear of brake rotors can cause reduced braking performance, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The brake rotors are warped or excessively worn
the steering wheel shakes or the vehicle pulsates when applying the brakes
the brake pads need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure and Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake lines can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a complete loss of braking ability and potentially a fire.
symptoms: The brake line breaks or leaks
smoke is visible from the brake system
a fire almost starts or starts.
